    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://www.bergzeit.co.uk/">Bergzeit</a> is one of the biggest German Outdoor Shops that has both Brick &amp; Mortar stores and an international online presence. Can this mountaineering and trekking shop come up with a good ultralight gear list?</p>

<p><img style="max-width:100%" src="https://farm8.staticflickr.com/7452/13422664394_47a78c0f70_b.jpg#tl-505313563879931906;1043138249" class="alwaysThinglink" /><script async="" charset="utf-8" src="http://hikinginfinland.com//cdn.thinglink.me/jse/embed.js"></script></p>

<!-- more -->

<p>I have been a <a href="http://www.bergzeit.co.uk/">Bergzeit</a> customer for quite a while, they usually have very competitive prices, regularly good discounts on gear and shipping Europe-wide is just 10€ and it’s fast - usually my order is on my doorstep within five days from clicking “Order”. Especially if you’re a climber then Bergzeit should be on your radar, but they also have a vast selection of high-quality hiking and backpacking gear - and you can make a very nice ultralight list, as you can see here: </p>

